net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data

Class Column

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data.Column

  • public class Column
extends Object
    The Column class holds properties for a column in a Table or a Tree.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • appendDisplayClass

        public void appendDisplayClass(String string)
        Append a value to the display class. If no display class is set the argument becomes the display class. Otherwise a space is appended to the existing display class and then the argument.
        Parameters:
        string - the string to append.

      • getPreferredWidth

        public Metric getPreferredWidth()
        Get the preferred width of the column. The medium should try to make the column width this size but may adjust if space will not allow or if there is extra space, while attempting to honor the minimum and maximum width. NOTE: this is no longer used. We may want to remove this method.
        Returns:
        Metric or null if not set.
